== Engines ==
[[File:2.4L Twin Cam.jpg|thumb|left|1997 Pontiac Sunfire Twin Cam engine]]
[[File:2003 Pontiac Sunfire Ecotec.JPG|thumb|left|2003 Pontiac Sunfire Ecotec engine]]
* 1995 – {{convert|138|cuin|L|1|abbr=on|disp=flip}} ''[[GM Quad-4 engine#LD2|Quad 4]] (RPO: LD2)'' [[Straight-4|I4]], 150&nbsp;hp (116&nbsp;kW) and {{convert|150|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}}
* 1995–1997 – {{convert|134|cuin|L|1|abbr=on|disp=flip}} ''[[GM OHV engine#2200 OHV|2200]] (RPO: LN2)'' I4, {{Convert|120|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|130|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}}
* 1998–2002 – {{convert|134|cuin|L|1|abbr=on|disp=flip}} ''[[GM OHV engine#2200 OHV|2200]] (RPO: LN2)'' I4, {{Convert|115|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|135|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}}
* 1996–2002 – {{convert|146|cuin|L|1|abbr=on|disp=flip}} ''[[GM Quad-4 engine#LD9|Twin Cam]] (RPO: LD9)'' I4, {{Convert|150|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|155|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}}
* 2002–2005 – {{convert|134|cuin|L|1|abbr=on|disp=flip}} ''[[GM Ecotec engine#L61|Ecotec]] (RPO: L61)'' I4, {{Convert|140|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|150|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}}

The base model had the 2.2&nbsp;L engine from 1994 until 2002. The GT trim level had an optional, more powerful 2.3&nbsp;L Quad 4 [[internal combustion engine|engine]] from 1994–1995, which was replaced by the 2.4&nbsp;L LD9 engine in 1995. The 2.3 and 2.4 litre engines were optional in the 2 and 4 door LS trim level. In 2003, both the 2.2&nbsp;L and the 2.4&nbsp;L engines were replaced by the 2.2&nbsp;L Ecotec engine, and would be the only powertrain available for the remainder of production.  The Ecotec engine was also an option for the 2002 model year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newcartestdrive.com/review-intro.cfm?Vehicle=2002_Pontiac_Sunfire&ReviewID=4160 |title=2002 Pontiac Sunfire Review, Prices, Photos |publisher=New Car Test Drive |date= |accessdate=2010-04-02}}</ref>

==Trim Levels==
The Sunfire could be purchased as a [[sedan (automobile)|sedan]], [[Coupé|coupe]], or [[convertible]].  All three variations came in the standard SE trim level.  An upscale GT trim level was available on the coupe and convertible. The GT trim level came standard with the 2.3 litre [[GM Quad-4 engine#LD9|LD2]] engine from 1994 to 1995 or the 2.4 litre [[GM Quad-4 engine#LD9|LD9]] "Twin Cam" engine (1996–2002), 16-inch alloy wheels, dual exhaust, and a more aggressive looking front fascia.  The SE trim was the standard for the Sunfire which included the 2.2 litre [[GM OHV engine#2200|2200 OHV]] Engine.  The 2.3/2.4 DOHC Engine was optional.  Both the SE and GT trim levels were dropped after the 2002 model year, along with the 2.2 OHV and 2.4 DOHC engines.  The 2.2 litre [[GM Ecotec engine#Ecotec|Ecotec]] was the only available engine as of the 2002 model year.<ref name="edmunds.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.edmunds.com/pontiac/sunfire/review.html |title=Pontiac Sunfire Review |publisher=Edmunds.com |date= |accessdate=2010-04-02}}</ref>

Originally, the convertible was only in the SE trim level until the 1999 model year where it became only available in the GT trim.  The convertible was discontinued after the 2000 model year. All Sunfire convertibles were assembled at the "Genesis" Lansing, Michigan Plant.<ref name="edmunds.com"/>

